PPP : Seruan Boikot Parpol Pendukung Perppu Ormas Bentuk Radikalisme   15:37 WIB Penulis: Antara ANTARA FOTO/Muhammad Arif Pribadi 
Ketua Umum DPP PPP Romahurmuziy mengkritisi seruan beberapa pihak agar memboikot atau tidak memilih partai politik pendukung Peraturan Pemerintah Pengganti Undang-Undang (Perppu) tentang Organisasi Kemasyarakatan, karena bisa menjurus pada radikalisme berbasis agama. 
"Seruan agar tidak memilih partai-partai yang mendukung Perppu Ormas menjadi UU, semua itu masalah pemahaman tentang agama yang pada titik tertentu bisa menjurus radikalisme berbasis agama," kata Romahurmuziy atau Romi dalam keterangan tertulisnya di Jakarta, hari ini. 
Hal itu disampaikan Romi saat menjadi pembicara evaluasi realisasi anggaran program Bimas Islam Triwulan III dan indeks kepuasan masyarakat terhadap pelayanan nikah tahun 2017 Kantor Wilayah Kementerian Agama Provinsi Jawa Timur, hari ini. 
Romi menilai isu tersebut akan tetap menjadi isu yang paling mengemuka dalam pembagunan sektor keagamaan sampai 5-10 tahun kedepan. Dia mengatakan, secara geografis Indonesia sangat mudah untuk di pecah belah sehingga dibalik seluruh konflik yang diagamakan, ada faktor non-agama namun banyak pihak yang terjebak dan menganggapnya sebagai konflik berbasis agama. 
"Konflik horizontal juga dilatarbelakangi dengan identitas-identitas yang sama sekali bukan identitas keagamaan. Karena itu, membaca konflik horizontal harus dengan kehati-hatian," ujarnya. 
Dia berharap masyarakat tidak mudah menganggap konflik horizontal sebagai konflik berbasis agama. Romi juga mengatakan, Indonesia sebagai negara berpenduduk muslim terbesar di dunia dan keempat terbesar penduduknya di dunia, menjadi laboraturium dari semua agama. 
Dia menjelaskan, salah satunya adalah Islam, sehingga laku dan gerak Islam di Indonesia, akan menentukan laku dan gerak Islam di dunia karena 1/8 penduduk Islam di dunia ada di Indonesia. (OL-7) Komentar

And includes this factoid: Historians suggest that this is part of the reason why Britons prefer tea nowadays. “Sri Lanka moved over to tea production” since coffee was no longer profitable, explains Aaron Davis, head of coffee research at Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew. Luckily for Asian producers, Britain was eager to switch its taste when their coffee supply vanished. I'm not sure that is true (uh, they drank beer and ale back then, not coffee). Indeed, a few medical history articles I read relate how the death rate went down in both Japan and later in England with tea drinking, although I suspect the reason was fewer deaths from water bourne illnesses. BBC article on tea drinking there. tea was expensive and used medicinally until Charles II's Portuguese wife introduced it as a routine pick me up. “When the queen does something, everyone wants to follow suit, so very, very gradually by the end of the 17th Century, the aristocracy had started sipping small amounts of tea,” Pettrigrew said. Of course, the upper class didn’t invent the ritual of tea-drinking themselves – they were imitators too. As Pettigrew recounted, “Until tea arrived with the Dutch, we [the English] didn’t know anything about tea. No sugar spoons, no cups, no tea kettles (only kitchen kettles), so we did what always happens: we copied the entire ritual from China. We imported [Chinese] tiny porcelain tea bowls, the saucers, the dishes for sugar, the small teapots.” wikipedia article on the tea service (i.e. cups and tea pots). here is an example at a British porcelain company: a full British "high tea" is a meal of delight, but the average Yank just plops a tea bag in a cup of very hot water, or nowadays, adds a teaspoon of powdered instant ice tea to the hot water. Lolo always drank his with sugar and calamansi (a small lime like fruit that grows on a bush in our front yard). when I worked in Africa, the tea was black and strong, brought to us in a pot covered with a "tea cosy" to keep it warm, and we added cream and sugar as desired. Here in the Philippines, they do have various teas, and serve ice tea in restaurants. Milk tea is also in vogue right now: But I dislike it beause it is very weak tea. They also sell ice tea in bottles, both green and regular, with various fruit joices added. We "Brew" tea in our coffeemate, but I usually just use the powdered drink with my water for meals, although now that we switched from city water which was highly chlorinated and tasted terrible, back to our deep well water, I am back to drinking water with my meals. posts.author: SLSene
posts.text:
20 hrs a week is 4 hours a day for a 5-day week, which is effectively half-time for the average 8:30am-5:30pm job with a 1 hr lunchbreak.
If by huge paycut you mean more than half, then I wouldn't do it. At my desk job, going part time often means having a lot less time to do the work but the work volume doesn't drop proportionately. I'd end up having to work a lot harder in the time that I'm at the office for significantly less pay.
It depends a lot on the nature of your work (whether it does go down proportionately with time spent) and whether you can stand the lifestyle change.
Personally I quit my job after first kid was born but went back to work when he was 7 months old because I was just not doing well at home, the pnd wouldn't lift. It miraculously disappeared when I started working again. There were other lifestyle factors involved but since then I have not stopped working or reduced hours after each kid. We get 16 weeks paid maternity leave here in Singapore, by law.

posts.author: Wake
posts.title: Impressive Super Mario Bros. Overworld and Underworld Themes Performed On Marimba
posts.text:
Impressive Super Mario Bros. Overworld and Underworld Themes Performed On Marimba Impressive Super Mario Bros. Overworld and Underworld Themes Performed On Marimba Wake November 7, 2017 Music No Comments 
How much practice did this require? This guy is amazing and his ability to hold onto all four of those mallets as he banged out these tunes is super impressive. The marimba is a very interesting instrument and is similar to a xylophone for those who are wondering, like myself. But the difference between them is that a xylophone is composed of wooden bars that are tuned to relevant notes, whereas the marimba is the same thing but with resonators that hang below the bars. The resonators enhance and balanced out the sound of the marimba in order to make it sound better. 
As you can hear in the clip the music being played seems to linger with each note until he keeps moving. It’s almost like listening to Calypso music in a way with its pleasant, constantly-moving sound and steady beat. You can actually see in your mind the game as it plays out, especially when the character makes his way down into the underworld as the music changes and you get the feeling of imminent danger lurking in all corners. From start to finish this piece is just awesome and the skill level of the musician is absolutely brilliant. I kind of wonder if he knows any other tunes and produce them in roughly the same way. 
The marimba seems to have been on the rise in popularity in many areas as of late and is thankfully a very pleasant sound that can accompany almost any tune and give it a nice playful quality that kind of eliminates any harsh or underwhelming tone that might exist. It’s not terribly hard to learn so long as a person is willing and can pay attention. In truth it’s just like anything else in that you learn depending on how much time you put into it. Tuning it and replacing parts would be far harder than learning to actually play, and listening to the instrument to know when it actually needs maintenance would also be beneficial. 
Super Mario Bros. is a tune that’s been improved on many times since its creation and nearly every style I’ve heard to this point has been vast improvement. It’s a little too late to go back and change the past at this time but just wondering what might have happened to the game if the music would have been professionally done in this manner is something to think about. The chances that it would have been ahead of its time are a little too easy to claim, plus the fact that the technology at the time to record such music wasn’t archaic but it also wasn’t up to the standard that it is now. 
I have to acknowledge the skill of the musician again though, since quite honestly playing the marimba as I said is not impossible, but it does require skill, focus, and some experience. Unless you know which note is which it’s nearly impossible to go just by ear alone and pick out the notes you need for a well-developed track.

thread.title_full: New rules needed to govern tech giants such as Google and Facebook, says summit chief - The National

posts.author: Reuters
posts.title: New rules needed to govern tech giants such as Google and Facebook, says summit chief
posts.text:
Web Summit's co-founder Paddy Cosgrave speaks during the inauguration of Web Summit, Europe's biggest tech conference. Pedro Nunes / Reuters Tech companies like Google and Facebook seem like monopolies and need new rules, the organiser of one of the world's biggest technology summits said.
Paddy Cosgrave, whose annual Web Summit takes place in Lisbon this week, joins growing calls for tighter regulation of big technology firms especially after news that Russia may have manipulated the last US election with political advertisements on Facebook.
He said recent initiatives by European Margrethe Vestager could bring big changes for big tech companies and help level the playing field in a sector which is having a profound impact on societies.
Vestager, who will speak at the Web Summit on Tuesday, has levied huge fines for unpaid taxes and unfair competition on big technology firms, including Apple, Google and Amazon in the past couple of years.
Read more:
Amazon slapped with EU order to pay Luxembourg more than €250 million in back taxes
EU accuses Facebook of giving misleading information during WhatsApp takeover
"In economic terms these (companies) would appear to fall into a classic definition of monopolies," Cosgrave told Reuters in an interview.
"And if she (Vestager) is successful she will probably set the standard for the rest of the world and will usher in a fundamental change in how the largest and most profitable companies in the history of the world are treated. This changes the playing field for all other companies."
Cosgrave said that new technology had been assumed by many to be just positive, but it often "can be incredibly disruptive".
He said the need for new rules was similar to past technological shifts such as the invention of cars.
"We had an operating system that, by and large with some modifications every decade, worked for the last 200 years," Cosgrave said.
"And then suddenly, you'd have to be naive or have your head buried in the sand, to not realise that the very fabric of our society, certainly western society, feels like it's getting pulled and stretched in weird ways. I think we need … a new operating system."
Web Summit has grown into one of the world's largest technology conferences, from 400 participants when it started in Dublin in 2010, to 59,000 participants this week. It started as a venue for tech start-ups and includes investors, but also increasingly politicians and regulators. U.N. Secretary General Antonio Guterres is scheduled to attend the Lisbon summit.
(Reporting By Axel Bugge, editing by Andrei Khalip and Emelia Sithole-Matarise)

" Adesso è davvero finita ". Mesta apertura nella prima pagina dedicata allo sport da parte della Gazzetta di Modena sul dramma della squadra cittadina: " Il Modena escluso dal campionato di C. Lo ha deciso il giudice sportivo della Lega Pro a seguito delle quattro rinunce comminando anche 10mila euro di multa ". Focus dettagliato nell'intera pagina dove si legge anche che " Il segretario tutela la sua immagine: Andrea Russo vuole giustizia e querela Antonio Caliendo ", quindi spazio all'assessore Guerzoni: " Taddeo chieda subito il fallimento.Giovedì scorso abbiamo scritto a Lega e Figc per salvare il vivaio ". Chiusura sull'attuale proprietario del club canarino: " Ma Aldo Taddeo aspetta i verdetti dei ricorsi. La proprietà prima di fallire vuole conoscere gli esiti sulle sconfitte a tavolino e la messa in mora ".
